-- African Development Bank Could Invest in Kalagadi's Project, Business Says
-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 2010-11-25T05:52:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-25/african-development-bank-could-invest-in-kalagadi-s-project-business-says.html
The African Development Bank may
invest in Kalagadi Manganese Ltd.’s 11 billion-rand ($1.6
billion) project to develop a manganese mine and sinter plant in
South Africa’s Northern Cape province, Business Report said.  The lender is considering an investment of as much as $150
million, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said, citing Godfrey
Mwindaare, chief investment officer at the bank’s private
industry unit.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  